docs.title: Home
docs.text:
LENS Project Thomas Fel, Thomas Serre {thomas_fel}@brown.edu Carney Institute for Brain Science, Brown University (Boston, USA), DEEL Team - Artificial and Natural Intelligence Toulouse Institute

This project is the result of several articles, the most notable ones being CRAFT · MaCo (coming soon) · Holistic (coming soon) · Sobol' attribution

The goal of this project is to use state-of-the-art explainability tools to explore the extent to which we can explain a ResNet50 trained on ImageNet. Each class in ImageNet has its dedicated page where you can see the concepts the model uses to classify that class. For each concept, a normalized importance level is assigned, indicating how crucial the concept is for the class. For instance, an importance level of 0.30 means that a concept contributes to 30% of the sum of logits for all points classified as such. The "Getting Started" page serves as an introduction, explaining how to interpret the results.

docs.title: Contributors
docs.text:
The dataset and the website itself were developed by Thomas Fel. However, the website relies on numerous works, with each member considered as a contributor to the LENS project.

CRAFT : Thomas Fel⭑, Agustin Picard⭑, Louis Béthune⭑, Thibaut Boissin⭑, David Vigouroux, Julien Colin, Rémi Cadène, Thomas Serre.

MaCo (coming soon) : Thomas Fel⭑, Thibaut Boissin⭑, Victor Boutin⭑, Agustin Picard⭑, Paul Novello⭑, Julien Colin, Drew Linsley, Tom Rousseau, Rémi Cadène, Laurent Gardes, Thomas Serre.

Holistic (coming soon) : Thomas Fel⭑, Victor Boutin⭑, Mazda Moayeri, Rémi Cadène, Louis Béthune, Léo Andeol, Mathieu Chalvidal, Thomas Serre.
